{
  "text": "We compared the lifespan of C. elegans under hyperglycemic conditions (16 mM glucose or 25 mM glucose) in the presence or absence of Olaparib. The C. elegans strains used in the lifespan studies were wild-type N2 Bristol and PARP1 knock-out mutant pme-1(ok988). Both strains were obtained from the Caenorhabditis Genetic Center (CGC, University of Minnesota). All nematodes were cultivated on nematode growth media (NGM) agar plates [CITATION_1] , which utilized living Escherichia coli bacteria OP50 as a food source, and were maintained at 20\u00b0C.",
